name: AZ Movers
review_text:
I have kept my old review at the bottom from our previous move, however, our most recent experience will be the last. We decided to use AZ as the experience previously had been great. This time round was shocking. On moving day, the movers were a no show. We kept trying the office number and emailing with no response. We had to end up getting another company to save the day. We did receive an email trying to explain the driver had an accident and the person in the office was on annual leave. I do not believe this for a second. Even if it was true was one man going to move a four bedroom house alone? No, there would have been the other 2 movers who could have phoned me.

I cannot recommend this company anymore after this experience. Please be aware if you pay using PayPal there is a charge of £35 and this is not refunded to you when they do not show up!

--

We used AZ movers for our recent house move and couldn't have been happier. We had a number of quotes and decided on AZ because of reviews and price.
On the move day we were in chaos. The developers had not confirmed key handover times or had any contact with us. The movers were patient and relaxed and really friendly . We did not feel rushed by them at all, which was really great considering everything was up in the air.
We will definitely use AZ movers for our next house move whenever that will be!
owner_answer: Hi Robyn! Thank You for your amazing words, we work hard on each of our moves and try our best to provide a stress free removal to all our customers and reviews like this push us to keep improving and looking forward!

name: AZ Movers
review_text: Used AZ movers for the first time to help me move my piano from Edinburgh to Glasgow. Their service was spot on from start to finish. They replied quickly to emails, took care of my piano in transit and were able to change the date of moving at short notice, which I was very appreciative of. Great value for money and would use their services again definitely.
owner_answer:
Hi Martha,

Thank You for your feedback! We did indeed help Martha with her upright piano move since we are specialist all Piano Moves are carried out by our amazing hardworking team.

Thank You Martha and we look forward to hearing from you again!

name: AZ Movers
review_text: AZ Movers dealt with my move from the Lothians to the south of England.  From initial discussions with Victoria who made things seamless and reassured me that they could handle my move; Sacha visiting on a snowy evening to estimate and then Damien and his team of superheroes who did the packing quickly and professionally and then arriving safely in my new home.  Can't recommend them enough.
owner_answer:
Hi Rosalind, 

Thank you for the wonderful review ! You have been a great customer.

name: AZ Movers
review_text:
My husband and I had a great experience with AZ Movers when we were moving from Edinburgh to London. The team is incredibly responsive, helpful, and friendly. They are extremely accommodating regarding dates, and the price was great.

After struggling to find a mover for a week, we contacted them as the 5th movers and requested a quote - within 30 minutes all our worries were over. The 4th mover never even responded. We would have went with AZ Movers from the start if we had known our lives would be that much easier.
owner_answer:
Thank You for your amazing review! We certainly did assist Simonida from Edinburgh to London it is one of our highest requested services in Edinburgh & Glasgow and we have the most competitive rates! 

Simonida was great to work with and We are happy to see she was satisfied with our service and we wish her the best!

name: AZ Movers
review_text:
We booked AZ Movers based on their online reviews and were not disappointed. On the day of our move we'd grossly underestimated how much we needed to pack and they helped us fill the final boxes. It took them most of the day to get us moved, but during that time the 2 movers didn't take any breaks, just an hour for lunch. Everything had to be carried up two flights of stairs as we've no lift and they did it with no complaints. Fast, efficient. One caveat, we went for the hourly rate instead of fixed price and we ended up paying slightly more but in the end we underestimated how much needed to be moved by about a third. If you're not sure, go for the fixed rate! And if you're not already pre-packed when ordering the move, assume you need one of the larger size vans. The woman we were dealing with advised us not to go for the smallest and we took her advice, in the end they could hardly close the door on the Luton van we ordered (which was massive).

All in all they made what's traditionally one of the most stressful parts of moving completely stress free. Strongly recommend.
owner_answer:
Hi Stephen!

We appreciate the review and the recommendation. We loved having you as a client.

Best Wishes!
AZ Movers

name: AZ Movers
review_text: We found AZ Movers on CompareMyMove and they offered us the most competitive price for a long distance move from Edinburgh to Oxfordshire. We were impressed  by them right from the start. They were cheerful, friendly and helpful at all times and were happy to work with our storage facility staff in Oxfordshire to unload and pack our rented storage room. We cannot speak too highly of them!
owner_answer:
Hi Rosie, 

Thank You for your feedback! AZ Movers does Alot of long distance moves and this allows us to be competitive in our pricing. Our move managers are diligent as well as friendly making sure all your requirements are met with absolutely no room for error.

name: AZ Movers
review_text: Good experience, booked a move from a 2-bed flat and paid just over £300 which was a lot less then other quotes. Very professional and efficient. They were very flexible and let me reschedule a booked viewing when my move got delayed by 3-4 months.
owner_answer:
Hi Marek,

I am happy to hear you had a good experience with us! AZ Movers is all about transparency and 
understanding that moving is stressful we actively try to make things easier for our customers and I am glad we lived up to our expectations! 

Thank You for the support!

name: AZ Movers
review_text:
I contacted AZ Movers recently to help me with the home move in Edinburgh. Victoria was very helpful. Right from providing quotes to arranging the right people - the team was very helpful.
Damien and his team did a fabulous job in helping on the day of move and carefully handing the items.
Would highly recommend AZ Movers!
owner_answer: Thank You Barath! Your feedback is very important to us!

name: AZ Movers
review_text: I was really happy with the service I received. I ordered an item from a store but the delivery drivers would not bring it up to my flat because it was too heavy. I called AZ Movers and they told me they could move it for me and arrived 1.5 hours later, exactly when they said they would and moved it for me. Polite, efficient service and reasonably priced. Would recommend and would use again.

name: AZ Movers
review_text:
Horror show which ive just been informed of.

Booked for a 2 van removal tomorrow  2/6/23.

Just been called with less than 24hrs notice to say they can't do the removal now and can't put anything in place to assist.

Absolutely disgusting customer service!!!!!!!

Thanks for putting extra pressure on an already terrible day

**UPDATE**

Ive noted AZ movers response which you can see........... however thats not why the job was cancelled, so even worse to try and deflect putting it back on the customer.
They didn't do the removal as with 12 hours notice they told me their 2 vans had broken down so the reply from them is utter garbage which in fairness links in well with them.
owner_answer:
Hello Mykiman, 

I am sorry you had this experience however we do request deposits immediately after a booking is confirmed by the customer and send reminders 3 days prior to the move date and during busy summer months if no deposit is paid we cannot guarantee a booking especially over the customers who had made their deposits for their moves. 

This is a standard practice with all moving companies and service industries, we hope to have served you.

name: AZ Movers
review_text: Had a very good experience with a part load from Edinburgh to Luton. AZ's initial offer was as cheap as any other I received, the office team offered an early date and explained the conditions about part loads well.  They responded quickly to phone calĺs and emails. During the move, the van team went out of their way to be helpful and did little extras I wouldn't necessarily have expected, to help. Would definitely use company again, and recommend to others. Wish AZ well!
owner_answer: Hi Christopher, Thank You for the great FeedBack, we appreciate it highly and are now working towards even better policies and services with out new and improved administration!

name: AZ Movers
review_text: Was extremely happy with service from AZMovers. Even with the short notice, the booked us in at a very affordable rate. Movers kept in contact with us throughout the day, they were very friendly, quick with the job and made a stressful experience very easy.

name: AZ Movers
review_text: Excellent recent experience with AZ Movers.  I needed things moved from storage to a house in Glasgow.  The two guys who did the removal were friendly, polite and very professional.  They worked quickly and took care of everything without a hitch.  Excellent value for money too and responded to emails quickly.
owner_answer: Thank You Ian, it was a great pleasure to help you with moving.

name: AZ Movers
review_text: The AZ Movers team were very unresponsive with their communication. I needed to prompt with every aspect of the transaction. They were not forthcoming about dates and times of removal and delivery and I continually had to follow up. The also changed the date of when they were picking up my property to put into storage on the day they were supposed to be coming, which was very stressful given I was selling my property and chose the day before my move specific to alleviate this stress. All in all, I wouldn't recommend this company.
owner_answer:
Hi Ashley, we apologise for your experience on the day of pick up we did mention a delay would occur as it was the days of lockdown everything was unexpected and we try to do our best with our given circumstances I recall that you were asked if you were okay with moving it before confirming to move and at that time you didn't mention anything instead confirmed the next available slot.

I had mentioned that we were looking for availability and therefore Didn't confirm dates and time until we did due to Christmas coming up you'd appreciate we are limited on availability.

We hope you understand that inspite Everything, we have been available on phone calls & other communications before this week were promptly responded to we still apologise for your experience and would like to assure you with the limited capacities every firm is working with we are all trying to do the best that we can.

name: AZ Movers
review_text: Would highly recommend AZ movers they quoted me a much lower price than anyone else and were very efficient with their communication. I gave them really short notice and they were able to help me out and fit me in. The removals guys were very professional and handled everything with care. Very good value for money

name: AZ Movers
review_text:
I have a lot of concerns about this company. I am not sure this company owns any of their own vans or if the actual owners even live in another country and just book contractors.

It all started well. Victoria was very polite and friendly, a man (Gabriel) arrived to measure up the house ready to quote us. We had quite a lot of stuff so I was very clear to show him around the whole house and show him everything that was going. He left and quoted us for 2 Luton vans. I did not think much at this point as my grandparents owned a removal company so I know that normally a removal company is responsible for quoting correctly. I then had a different company come and quote me (a real removal company... we will get to that later), the person checking told me we needed their biggest lorry, I told him I had been quoted for 2 Luton vans and he said he was not sure it would all fit on 2 Luton vans, that I should be careful, it was the companies responsibility if that was what was quoted, but it could cause issues if they couldn't fit it all in the van as they would then have to arrange something and it could delay the move.

Unfortunately due to issues with our moving date, we couldn't book anyone in until the last minute. On the Tuesday, we had the go ahead that we SHOULD be moving on the following Sunday, but it would not be confirmed until Thursday. AZ Movers were the only company that had quoted me that were still available. I asked Victoria if she was able to hold the spot for me for 2 days just to get it all confirmed. She agreed. On Thursday at 16:10 I had confirmation so I emailed Victoria to confirm that booking. On Friday she came back to me to say that the vans had now gone but that she was trying to sort something out. I was a bit irritated and she mentioned about the system updating overnight and the vehicles not being available. Believing this to be an Edinburgh based company with their own vans, I didn't give this a second thought. I now believe that because Victoria is actually based in Pakistan (we will get to this later) she did not receive my email until the next morning (as it would have been much later than 4pm when she received the email). Victoria managed to get someone who was able to complete the move, but the price had increased by an extra 10% due to having to find extra vans.
Frustrated but understanding that maybe there was a glitch that meant that someone else in her team must have booked the vans that Victoria had reserved for me, I accepted the extra charge.

So then moving day arrived. The 2 Luton vans arrived and the drivers asked if Victoria was there. There was some confusion about the drivers having not realised they were booked as a third party but I had assumed that could be the case rather than it being AZ vans due to the booking issue. The guys that arrived were really great, professional and friendly but this was their first job with AZ so not normally AZ movers, therefore I cannot say what the normal drivers are like. They did raise concerns on seeing the house that there was more stuff than they had space for. They told me that Victoria had not sent them all the pictures, and if they had seen them, they would have said at the time. So I started dismantling every single piece of furniture, just to give us every single cm of space. (even though when Gabriel had come round he had said I would not need to). The vans loaded and there was still around half a trucks worth of stuff left AND we had decided the day before to leave our large fridge. So we had been massively underquoted. When I got the details from the drivers for Victoria they gave me her number via WhatsApp. The number for Victoria came up as in Pakistan. When I called the office numb I had realised it was being forwarded to a mobile number, but I assumed due to covid that Victoria was just working from home. I had been right. Office address is a mailbox with nearly 1000 companies registered there. Wanted to charge an extra £1000 to complete the move. Refused to accept removal companies charge for the move not the van hire. AVOID
owner_answer:
We did in fact serve Wayne, He is an authentic customer with good and polite communication, so a customer that any company would like to have. We can't fault on his professional and polite approach; the move was from Edinburgh all the way to Ipswich.

However, we would like to highlight a few things here, which may have caused some confusion, especially for timings & delays which was the main concern on the day.

This job was booked very last minute, on the 24th about an hour before the offices close. The calendar was clear of any moves at this point, I requested a deposit, but Mr. Wayne said he would pay this in the morning – note we book on a first come first serve basis. By the morning, my colleague updated the system and there were jobs booked and deposits paid. I immediately informed Wayne in the morning, he had already paid his deposit, so I offered a refund, or I could take measures to sort it out – he chose us to sort it out so I called up a colleague who had used Thomas before and spoke highly of him, so we arranged Thomas for Wayne’s move – and Wayne was happy with this but there was a price increase and we again gave Wayne the option of a full refund but he declined and agreed to pay the additional fee. We sent Thomas (The contractor) all the information we had comprehensive images and videos and Thomas confirmed that 2 large luton vans will be plenty the same opinion AZ Movers employees had - he still took one standard luton van and one custom built large Low loader just in case, despite almost everything fitting in to the van there was a lot of random smaller pieces that were scrap like – we realized this wouldn’t fit. This caused rightful stress to the customer who out of Frustration may have not realized that it is not a business’s responsibility to move more than what was agreed in the contract and all readers would appreciate a contract works both ways we still went out of the way to reschedule a 3rd van and charged cost price for it ofcourse - which was a small transit van since there wasn’t a lot left behind but he ended up sorting it out himself. Wayne seemed to be okay with everything and we moved on from this.

It is unfortunate that Wayne seems it relevant to point out that, I, Victoria am based in Pakistan Thrice I do find it offensive. Nevertheless, I do realize Wayne spoke out of Frustration. I am now back in Scotland should anyone else care where I work from 😊 you are welcome to visit me 😌.

Most if not All moving firms in Edinburgh specifically - have only Logistics offices if any one is interested to see our logistics office, our own vehicles and our storage space please feel free to request it and we shall be completely Transparent.

Wayne failed to see our efforts to book and arrange such a large removal in such short notice, even with a lot of our efforts and hard work Wayne ended up withholding paying us at the time of delivery which made both me and the “ Contractors “ very uncomfortable, I signed off and let the boys handle payment with Wayne directly to ensure my boys got paid since Wayne had made it clear he wasn’t paying us a dime.

We wish Wayne the best and apologize if he feels we failed him, but we do hope that now that things have settled down Wayne sees our efforts to put him first.

Regards,

Victoria, Nicole, Zahra, George and all the other staff members who worked hard.

name: AZ Movers
review_text: My experience with azmovers was really good. All the staff was very friendly and cautious. The job done as it was arranged, fast, without any damage on furniture or walls. Professional and good value for money company. Highly recommended. Thanks very much guys!

name: AZ Movers
review_text:

Well done azmovers, five stars awarded..

name: AZ Movers
review_text: Thanks so much to Victoria and George for organising my move from London to Scotland. name: AZ Movers
review_text: AZ Movers were very helpful at finding us a van at short notice and communicated well with us. The guys driving were really efficient and went out of their way to help us load up/load out the van. I would highly recommend this company to everyone!

name: AZ Movers
review_text:
We used AZ movers from Edinburgh the first time and we were positively surprised by their efficiency and friendliness.
Within three hours our complete furniture got moved down three floors and up two floors. The two lads and the van did a great job and took care about our furniture which they covered with towels and blankets to protect them during the move in the van.

owner_answer:
Dear David,
Thank You for the review, we loved dealing with you as well and appreciate a great customer! We really appreciate it and hope you'll recommend us to friends & family.
AZ Movers Team

name: AZ Movers
review_text:
We booked AZ Movers Edinburgh taking our things from London to Peebles. Overall, this was the worst customer service and experience I have ever had. They are still trying to chase us for money that was never agreed!

Pre-pick up date:
We initially provided a window from the 8-15 October for a partial load. While we understand we could have been given any date within that window, we requested a date towards the end of the window and were assured this would be taken into account.
At this stage we were told the confirmation of our pick up date would be confirmed by the end of September - having chased on multiple occasions, we finally received confirmation on 6 October - a week from when we should have been notified and two days before the pick up date leaving a small window to pack our belongings.
Due to the small window, we had little choice but to book our own van at a later date. We realise this was our choice to change it but wanted to acknowledge the lack of communication/delay in confirmation leading up to this point.
We received the below confirmation noting an all-inclusive cost for our own van. At this point we were not made aware of sending an updated inventory list and that should we have more items we would be charged more.
"As discussed you’ve been rescheduled for 15th of October collection in London for £900 all-inclusive.
Please make the remaining payment of £500 on the day of collections"
After leaving a voicemail and calling back, we were able to speak to the team who outlined our pick up time would be between 3-4pm on the 15th.
We left another voicemail on the morning of the 15th to confirm time-slot, did not receive a call back, and chased to find out the van would not arrive until around 7pm.
Our tenants were due to move in on Friday afternoon, so we had a cleaner booked for Thursday and I was booked on a train based on the 3-4pm window provided.
Due to the scheduling issue, Victoria rescheduled to the Friday morning at 9am and estimated the belongings would be in Peebles around 6/7pm.

Day of pick up
The staff arrived just after 9am and noted the discrepancy between the list and what I noted.

After calls with Victoria, I was made aware that an updated inventory list should have been sent and that costs for greater than 1/2 a van would be £1,200.

The staff started loading at 9:20am and were finished by 9:45am. I believe our things would have made up a maximum of 1/2 van but likely closer to 1/3 if it was packed properly. So we we didn't feel the £1,200 charge even matches the job. The van already had items in it and the staff mentioned they were picking up bikes on their way. So from my understanding, they had taken our dedicated van and added extra bookings.

Because of this service, we've had to rebook cleaners multiple times and postpone our tenants arrival time on the Friday. My partner travelled up to Scotland to meet the van and instead of having a day and a half to sort, had a few hours on Friday night and left to come back to London Saturday morning.

We also found the short time window provided by Victoria, at 13:50, of paying an invoice (which was not attached to the email) by close of play before starting the process with a debt collector unacceptable and unprofessional. Even though I responded within an hour to escalate, we heard nothing back and had had to call to get answers before the set deadline.

Overall this has been the worst customer experience we’ve ever had. As a removal company, they know how much planning and time goes into a move. This company has made this whole process more complicated and we feel it is unacceptable to pay any additional charges. We've been completely messed around and we actually should receive a partial refund for the lack of communication, delay in our move and other incurred costs to us.

name: AZ Movers
review_text: I had dealt with Victoria James from the office , who handled my calls and scheduled the appointment promptly. The guys who came to do the work were professional and finished all the work in time. Thanks to AZ movers for making my move so comfortable and stress free. I would definitely recommend them!!!
owner_answer: Thank You! It was a pleasure to work with you.

name: AZ Movers
review_text: I phoned the day before and Victoria helped me organise a delivery for next day. She accepted my request for one delivery man and trusted me when I said my son would be available at both sides. The driver arrived late but he phoned ahead to tell me of his delay. The van was large enough to take 4 wardrobes and the delivery guy secured them all very well. I will use AZ Movers again for my next delivery, which will be in a few weeks time, as they are very reasonably priced and met all my requirements. Thanks
owner_answer:
Jennifer,

Thanks for the Kind words, We will be more than happy to assist! You know where to find us!

Best Wishes,
AZ Movers Edinburgh

name: AZ Movers
review_text: They were half an hour late, and I had to phone the office to find out what was going on, however aside from that I had a great experience with AZ Movers. Calum and Keith were really nice and nothing was too big an ask for them. They had my entire flat cleared and everything moved into my new one in under an hour. Was very impressed with the service. Highly recommended.
owner_answer: Thank you Stu for your feedback! It is very important for us. We took note of your experience and made sure our process now is improved.

name: AZ Movers
review_text:
I used AZ Movers to move my one bed flat contents into storage and they offered the cheapest quote. Like Tom's review previously, I think it's fair to give an overview of the pros and cons of using this removal company:

Cons
1. Two removal guys showed up on the day but forgot key to lorry door padlock, so they couldn't open the back of the lorry and had to go to a garage to get the padlock opened.
2. About 45 mins later when the packers returned, they asked me where the boxes and packaging materials were. I was confused as I thought the packers brought them on the day of the move. They said the boxes should have been delivered in advance of the move but no boxes had been delivered to my flat.
3. No prior communication from AZ movers to confirm the boxes would be delivered to my address. If I had been aware of this I would have made prior arrangements to be home that day to accept delivery.
4. The packers then had to leave again to go get boxes and packaging material for the move.
5. While the packers were away buying more boxes, the boxes that I had pre-ordered from AZ Movers showed up at a neighbour's flat. They were extremely small for the contents of a one bed flat and only a tiny amount of bubble wrap was provided. If I had known AZ Movers provided terrible boxes and packaging then I would have gone elsewhere to buy my own.
6. Due to all the delays, the move was running late and we still had to unpack the van at the other end and move everything into storage before the storage unit closed, so I assisted the lads with some of the packing and moving contents into the van. I was happy to help to move things along but some customers may not be so understanding especially if they pay extra for a packing service.

Pros:

1. The packers were hardworking on the day and very friendly. If it wasn't for them buying more boxes and a roll of bubble wrap when the delivery didn't show up, then we wouldn't have got the contents fitted into the original boxes provided by AZ Movers.

2. The company offers a very cheap rate for moving.

All in all, it worked out ok in the end but compared to other removal companies in Edinburgh this is not what I would describe as a professional removal service. I wouldn't use them again and won't be recommending them to others. I would say this is a good example of you get what you pay for.
owner_answer:
Dear Elle Mcmaster,

We appreciate the honest feedback, as a company we do take responsibility for the communication error on our part and it hadn't met our full standards we would like to assure you and our future customers that AZ Movers takes into consideration all feedback positively and try to improve.

We have realized the packing material company ( 3rd Party not associated with AZ Movers ) is not the most reliable & high standard service provider and this has been realized due to the numerous  reviews we received regarding. Hence, we would like to assure you we will no longer be using them and have officially removal them from our vendors and now sell packing material on our website directly.

Since, We were at error and all this could have been avoided should we have communicated effectively we will call you ( Miss Elle Mcmaster ) and discuss what we can do to make you feel more secure and ensure you that we are indeed professionals who take full responsibility & look out for all our customers should we cause them inconvenience. Please get in touch so we can discuss a partial refund since we feel obliged to pay back customers should they have had to assist the movers especially since we were hired to do it all.

We hope to solve any concerns and add more pros to your list. :)

Regards,
Zahra P.
Director

name: AZ Movers
review_text: AZ Removals were great from start to finish.  Dealing with Victoria was a pleasure she was very professional and every question I asked of her she came back promptly.  The two removal guys were absolutely brilliant they arrived on time and dealt with a third floor move so quickly and efficiently that I cannot praise them enough.  Their quote was one of the most reasonable ones and I took a chance on that and so glad that I did! I will definitely use them again as they genuinely deserve their five stars!

name: AZ Movers
review_text:
**Please note - after leaving my review, AZ movers have made contact and provided a partial refund, which was gratefully received. I hope the points in my review can be used by the company to make constructive improvements.

Tom Carter

I used AZ movers as they were cheaper than the other quotes. My wife advised me against choosing the cheapest quote, but I ignored her. Here is my balanced review.

Negatives:
1. Two guys turned up to pack the night before but thought they were here to remove already packed items.
2. No delivery of packing goods ie, boxes, tape etc. The 'packers' then had to go to the nearest warehouse and then start packing late.
3. Packers clearly ran out of steam/ couldn't be bothered and left 30% of things in the house unpacked. Very kindly left us a note saying 'we have left some spare boxes, please feel free to continue packing your stuff into them' - despite is paying for a comprehensive packing service.
4. Two lads the next day then managed to smash some crystal wedding gifts.
5. Wardrobe doors deeply scratched.
6. Staff very happy to undermine their own bosses/managers, which raises concerns about the working relationships within the company.

Positives:
1. Was cheaper than the rest
2. The guys who did the moving part of the job were lovely and worked very hard all day without moaning, for which we are grateful for (despite the above breakages).

In summary:
Would I use them again - no
Would I recommend them to others - no
Always listen to your wife - sadly they are usually right!
owner_answer:
Dear Tom Carter,

We apologize for any inconveniences caused to you & Your wife, AZ Movers is changing how they operate from here on forth since it effects us immensely to know our customers are not happy and we realize that there are communication errors.

We have offered all customers a partial refund to ensure customer satisfaction & we hope that you can accept our apology and the partial refund by contacting the office.

AZ Movers is setting the bar high and we assure everyone reading and Tom that this will not be happening again. We take our feedback seriously and will ensure that all jobs here on forth are dealt with the high standards that we promise to deliver.

This is why as the director I shall be personally looking into this matter, Your feedback is highly appreciated.

Regards,
Zahra P.
Director of AZ Movers LTD

name: AZ Movers
review_text:

Kevin

Kevin,

Thank You for the amazing feedback, you've been a great customer and we hope to serve you again.

name: AZ Movers
review_text:
Don't touch.
Turned up in the morning one hour late. The amount of damage they did to walls, bannister and furniture was unbelievable. They even left a pushbike outside my old house (not mine!) as they didn't want it. I did ask and pay for another man and van at short notice which ended up being the same guys doing 2 trips. We were moving 50 miles away. At 8pm I told them to leave the rest of my stuff as I was exhausted. I have contacted the company about most of the damage and the bike being left but they replied they had received my email and then nothing. Victoria was lovely to deal with but aftercare is appalling.

name: AZ Movers

name: AZ Movers
review_text:
If I could leave a "no star" review, I would. My experience with these jokers has been shambolic to say the least.  They came to my house to quote & quoted to supply packaging, pack all my possessions, move everything then clean my house.
The wrong size boxes arrived, they pitched up late to pack then ran out of boxes within 2 hours, so couldn't finish the packing on the allocated day. Arrived the next day at 10am instead of 8am like their website says, carried on packing, then only managed to move half my possessions on the moving day. That night I got an email saying it would be an additional £720 if I wanted them to complete the move the next day!
Furthermore, they damaged my leather lounge suites, damaged my walls, used my tools (& lost them) to dismantle furniture & lost my bolts for a bed. Then because they couldn't finish the move, the cleaning had to be delayed to the Wednesday. They then changed that to the Friday but I had to return keys to the agents, so I couldn't use their cleaning service. They have refused to return the whole amount quoted for the cleaning & have refunded £20 for the damages to my walls while the invoice for the cleaning is £145.
Stay away from these guys, all they do is apologise for their incompetence & mistakes but don't take responsibility!
owner_answer:
We did in fact provide Mr. Puren with our services, but would like to provide our accounts of events so the readers can make an informed decision.

We quoted him £1070 (with a discount) The terms were 2 Van Loads mentioned in written, since they had a lot more things.
We did send the wrong sized boxes which we accepted we arranged for more boxes and offered to do a 3rd van load free of cost plus 1 or 2 hours more for packing if it was done the same day.

The price was quoted for a last minute removal for 2 more van loads we charged £720 *we weren’t available last minute* – which upset him but we were booked.

It's a shame Mr. Puren hasn’t mentioned we paid him for his spanner & bolts without questions (My guys did not agree to any of it and we paid cancellation fees via our own pocket for the cleaning as a gesture of good will. Unfortunately, we did indeed mark the wall due to a minor slip - we offered to fix it Mr. Puren was nice enough to have refused the offer at the time of the move but then proceeded to send an invoice for a 1”x 2” mark of £145 which included all other damages in his 5 bedroom house under his own company name - we proceeded by paying a small part of the fee that we saw fit.

Due to unavailability - after the cancelled date - we refunded £150 but Mr. Puren wanted a refund for £195 which is more than he had paid for the service itself, all together AZ Movers paid 15% of the removal from its own pocket in order to address his claims and ensure satisfaction – No Sofa’s were damaged by us or as every other issue we would have addressed this as well.

Despite all our efforts Mr. Puren has not realized that we put him first and addressed all his claims and continuously apologized & worked towards a solution but after reading his own Companies reviews for PPM Edinburgh I have realized that Mr. Puren in the past has made the same claims with many of his own customers which we frown upon.

As you can see from our previous reviews, we serve several hundred customers every year, and we take pride in our customer services. We hope that all readers will take into consideration that we are a genuine local business with satisfied customers and this review does not reflect the service that our customer’s experience.

name: AZ Movers
review_text:
SCAM ALERT!!!!!!! I booked this company last year and paid a hefty £240 deposit. After this, they became COMPLETELY UNRESPONSIVE for several weeks. They don't answer emails, they don't respond to voicemails. I then tried to cancel my booking due to their unresponsiveness and Victoria (who seems to be the only person working in this company) then started to respond and became completely unprofessional. She LIED about conversations we'd had, she accused me of lying, and she even CHANGED THE TERMS AND CONDITIONS WITHOUT INFORMING ME during our discussion to try and make me ineligible to get my deposit back. Since then, I have had a case opened with both TRADING STANDARDS and the SHERRIFF COURT to try and retrieve my money and they will not respond to either of them.

I do not believe for a second that any of these positive reviews are genuine customers since they have completely scammed me out of £240 during the most stressful period of my life! The stress that this company have cause me has resulted in a chronic medical condition and 8 months after paying for a service, I still have nothing in return.

I HONESTLY DONT KNOW HOW THESE PEOPLE SLEEP AT NIGHT!
owner_answer:
Dear Gill,

(Update: We have still not been presented with Gills case, we have tried to get in touch but have had no response )

I, being the director of AZ Movers can assure you that our business is not a Scam but actually a genuinely registered business that is highly regarded in Edinburgh as a professional firm.

Every business charges cancellation charges as do we. Our cancellation policy has never changed, it has been the same through out 2017-2021. I can assure you I am not aware of any officials ( trading standards ) that have gotten in touch. We have the right to change or terms and conditions whenever necessary however I am the only one authorized to do so and Guarantee that it isn't possible.

Nevertheless! If you have a genuine case I will personally refund you as a gesture of good will, feel free to draft an email and send it to me azmoversuk@gmail.com

It is common practice to charge cancellation fees, especially if cancellations are made last minute this is because we have already put resources towards the move and allocated times and have denied other customers who may want the same date as you. Our labors are still paid for the day and administration, paper work has been done this is behind the scene efforts that unfortunately aren't available for the public to see and there are charges in place to protect us, that is the reason a deposit is taken In the first place.
We offer free date changes as well as free postponing this is because we know that the job will still take place today or 6 months from now. However, we do not offer free cancelations nor does any other business in Edinburgh as the industry is small we all have the same rules.

Your frustrations are justified, when we pay an amount we expect a service to take place but if the service hasn't taken place for reasons not concerning us there is not much we can do, this was especially true in your case. I have offered you a good deal if you're interested why not get in touch via email and if I believe you had a genuine case I will personally refund you and will be more than happy for you to share more honest views on a public forum rather than one sided views which are incorrect and not factual.
